{"title_page": "Journey (Yeng Constantino album)", "text_new": "{{Infobox album\n| name       = Journey\n| type       = Studio\n| artist     = [[Yeng Constantino]]\n| cover      = Album Journey cover.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = February 29, 2008\n| recorded   =\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Pop rock]]\n| length     = 50:37\n| label      = [[Star Music]]\n| producer   = Dream Big Productions\n| prev_title = [[Salamat (album)|Salamat]]\n| prev_year  = 2007\n| next_title = [[Lapit]]\n| next_year  = 2009\n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = Journey'\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = Habambuhay\n | single1date = December 2007\n | single2     = Ikaw Lang Talaga\n | single2date = March 2008\n | single3     = Di Na Ganun\n | single3date = August 2008\n | single4     = Himig ng Pag-ibig\n | single4date = October 2008\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''Journey''''' is the second album by a [[Filipino people|Filipina]] singer - songwriter [[Yeng Constantino]], released on February 29, 2008 via [[Star Music]]. The album contains twelve tracks: six were composed by Constantino, two were a collaboration of Constantino and Morning Glory.<ref>{{cite web | title = Yeng Constantino shares her \"Journey\" of self-discovery | url=http://www.pep.ph/guide/1673/Yeng-Constantino-shares-her-Journey-of-self-discovery | accessdate = 2008-03-05}}</ref> Journey sold more than 15,000 copies and is certified Gold. It was followed by her third album, [[Lapit]].\n\n==Track listing==\n# \"''Di Na Ganun''\" (Constantino) -  4:57\n# \"''Ikaw Lang Talaga''\" (Constantino) -  2:52\n# \"''Promise''\" (Constantino) - 4:23\n# \"''Pili Ka Lang''\" (Constantino) -  3:55\n# \"''Tao Lang Ako''\"  ( Constantino ) - 4:44\n# \"''What About Us''\"  (Constantino) -  4:33\n# \"''Himig Ng Pag-ibig''\"  (Lolita Carbon) -  4:21\n# \"''Bakit Nga Ba''\" ( Annabelle Ragalado-Borja [Words] & Allan Danug [Music] ) - 3:49\n# \"''If You Go''\" (Eman Abatayo) -  4:58\n# \"''Why Can't You''\" (Constantino & Morning Glory) -  4:03\n# \"''Tala''\" (Constantino & Morning Glory) -  4:09\n# \"''Habambuhay''\" ( Annabelle Ragalado-Borja [Words] & Allan Danug [Music] ) - 3:53\n\n==Singles==\n* '''Habambuhay''' was a single, used as the Official Theme Song for the 2008 blockbuster Movie, \"Sakal, Sakali, Saklolo\" starring [[Judy Ann Santos]] & [[Ryan Agoncillo]] where it is nominated for the Best Theme Song of the Year.<ref>{{cite web | title = PMPC announces nominees for the 24th Star Awards for Movies | url=http://www.pep.ph/news/17306/PMPC-announces-nominees-for-the-24th-Star-Awards-for-Movies/4/2 | accessdate = 2008-04-29}}</ref>\n* '''Ikaw Lang Talaga''' this was the second single off this album. This was used as official theme song for the Taiwannovela [[Why Why Love]] & [[Miss No Good]] starring [[Rainie Yang]].<ref>{{cite web | title = If We Fall In Love - Ikaw Lang Talaga, Miss No Good OST | url=http://nmagz.wordpress.com/2009/08/24/ikaw-lang-talaga/ | accessdate = 2009-08-29}}</ref>\n* '''Di Na Ganun''' was the third single, was used as sub-theme for the television series starring [[Anne Curtis]], The Wedding. As well as ''Promise''.\n* '''Himig Ng Pag-Ibig''' was the last single, it was used as Official Theme song for the Hit Primetime Fantasy starring [[Anne Curtis]], [[Dyosa]].<ref>{{cite web | title = Himig ng Pag-ibig (DYOSA OST)- Yeng Constantino | url=http://nmagz.wordpress.com/2009/08/24/ikaw-lang-talaga/ | accessdate = 2009-01-01}}</ref>\n\nJust Like for her previous album, Most of Constantino's Singles from the Journey Album were used as theme songs for [[ABS-CBN]]'s Teleserye & Movie Outfit.\n\n==Chart performance==\n===Album===\n\"Journey\", had debuted at No. 14 on March 15, 2008 and peaked at No. 8 by the end of the month. It stayed for three months in the Top 20 Albums of 2008.<ref>{{cite web | title = Journey Album Debuted at No.14, Odyssey's Album Chart: March 15, 2008| url=http://www.titikpilipino.com/charts/top10.php?releasedate=2008-03-15 | accessdate = 2008-03-15}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Yeng Constantino 's Salamat & Journey Album Chart Performance History! |url=http://inyi.multiply.com/journal/item/40/Yeng_Constantino_s_Salamat_Journey_Album_Chart_Performance_History_ |accessdate=2009-11-10 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110714131705/http://inyi.multiply.com/journal/item/40/Yeng_Constantino_s_Salamat_Journey_Album_Chart_Performance_History_ |archivedate=2011-07-14 }}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Date\n! Peak<br/>position\n|-\n| 2008\n| align=\"center\"|8\n|}\n\n==Certification==\nJourney's Gold Certification was given to Yeng in August 2009 at [[ASAP (variety show)]].\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Region (Provider)\n! Certification\n! Sales\n! References\n|-\n| [[Philippines]] <small>([[Philippine Association of the Record Industry|PARI]])\n| Gold\n| 15,000^\n| <ref>{{cite web|title=Yeng Constantino's Journey Gold Album Award in ASAP 09 with Morning Glory |url=http://www.urdumaza.com/videos/watch/BLL29ZxgF7w/yeng-constantinos-journey-gold-album-award-in-asap-09-with-morning-glory.html |accessdate=2009-03-20 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110717173431/http://www.urdumaza.com/videos/watch/BLL29ZxgF7w/yeng-constantinos-journey-gold-album-award-in-asap-09-with-morning-glory.html |archivedate=July 17, 2011 }}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Awards and recognition==\n'''2009'''\n* WRR 101.9 WAKI OPM Award: \"Best Album of the year\" - \"Journey\".<ref>{{cite web | title = Pinoy bands, singers honored at Waki Awards | url=http://telebisyon.net/balita/Pinoy-bands-singers-honored-at-Waki-Awards/artikulo/59365/ | accessdate = 2009-04-30}}</ref>\n\n'''2008'''\n* Pop Music Video (\"Himig ng Pag-Ibig\"): ASAP Pop Viewer's Choice Awards 2008<ref>{{cite web | title = ASAP \u201908\u2019 announces the Pop Viewer\u2019s Choice Awards winners , www.abs-cbn.com - Napoleon Quintos (16Nov08)  | url=http://www.sarahgeronimo.com/forums/index.php?showtopic=15341&pid=1108883&mo